<TITLE> 1 crore families to get VGF rice for Eid </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 28 (bdnews24.com)The government will distribute 10 kg of rice each among one crore families of 481 upzillas that have Vulnerable Group Feeding cards before Eid-ul-Azha. Public communications officer of the food ministry, SM Golam Kibria, told bdnews24.com, "One lakh metric tonne of rice has been allocated for implementing this project. "Allotted rice under district authorities will have to be collected by Nov 15. Costs covering transportation of rice and other activities have been allocated." He said a circular has been issued asking the district administrators to take necessary steps informing local MPs. The circular also urges strict compliance with VGF project regulations. It says it has to be ensured that two members of same family do not get VGF card
